history.content:
C8 is set up to allow time conflicts and it WILL be webcast.

However, if you haven't enrolled yet, you are too late! Enrollment for this class (including access to the wait list) is CLOSED. Demand for the class is too high and the class will not expand further.

children.subject: Please send an email to SISHELP@berkeley.edu. This is probably a system glitch that only they can fix. I set the class to allow time conflicts but I've heard some reports of issues. They should be able to help.

Thanks! I am currently number 230 position on the WL and I have been receiving the following notification from the CalCentral multiple times so I am not sure what to do about it since my discussion session that is conflicted with C8 lecture does not have another option:

You have NOT been enrolled from the wait list into the following class:

Term: 2018 Fall

Class: COMPSCI      C8 

Section: 001

Reason: Time conflict with another section.

As neither class allows time conflict enrollments, you will remain on the waitlist unless or until you resolve the time conflict.

You are responsible for dropping yourself from the waitlist if you do not wish to enroll in the requested class. You are responsible for any deadlines to drop yourself from the waitlist or the class if you are enrolled in a future date.

history.content: Will Data 8 lectures accommodate time conflicts and have webcasts? Thanks!
